&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Physician&#39;s Associate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kingston Hospital is a vibrant place to work and develop your career. One of the few hospitals to be rated as &lt;strong&gt;Outstanding&lt;/strong&gt; by the CQC. It also a happy place to work with top marks for Staff Engagement in the nationwide NHS staff survey. Staff wellbeing and happiness are at the core of delivering the best in patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint two exceptional individuals to join our Care of the Elderly department as Physician’s Associates. There are replacement substantive posts in the department of geriatric medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kingston Hospital is on the edge of the beautiful Richmond Park in South West London with close links to our local community, tertiary centres and Kingston University.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There has been significant investment in the Care of the Elderly department and we are developing innovative pathways of care for our frail elderly patients both throughout the hospital and across the whole local health economy . This post represents an exciting opportunity to join a dynamic clinical team and to contribute to the ongoing development of high-quality services to older patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Shaila Suleman&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Assistant Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address shaila.suleman@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0208 934 2478&lt;/p&gt;
